The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and students at the College of Charleston in South Carolina. The Vice President discusses various topics including her "Fight for Our Freedoms" tour, voting rights, LGBTQ+ rights, gun violence, and climate change. She emphasizes the importance of young people getting involved and using their voices to make a difference. The Vice President also addresses concerns about reproductive healthcare and outlines the government's efforts to address climate change and fund initiatives to combat its impacts. She encourages the students to be ambitious, not to be deterred by obstacles, and to be mindful of the impact their activism can have on people around the world.